It is extremely sneaky and hard to understand since it happens in a simple Metamask notification that we usually accept, almost out of muscles memory.

What is interesting about this phishing attack is that unlike Web2, where the goal is to get your username and password, this one targets your wallet directly by approving their own smart contracts which gives them extensive control over your NFTs.
It look like the attacker(s) had a very sophisticated phishing attack, by mimicking OpenSea in many ways, through similar looking website to email.

I am waking up to calls that OpenSea got hacked - it does not seems that way.
